35:28.168 --> 35:30.168
Dave?

35:30.212 --> 35:32.879
- Now, the Zweihander was known
as a weapon of intimidation,

35:32.923 --> 35:35.215
and to test the sharpness
of your edge,

35:35.259 --> 35:38.009
I'm going to cut into this
bundle of sugarcane twice--

35:38.053 --> 35:40.095
once with either side.

35:40.139 --> 35:42.055
Jay, you're up first.
Are you ready?

35:42.099 --> 35:44.432
- Ready as I'm ever gonna be.

35:44.476 --> 35:46.685
I know my blade's sharp.
I know it'll do good.

35:46.728 --> 35:48.520
<i> I'm expecting something epic.</i>

35:48.564 --> 35:50.188
But, until it's
really put to the test,

35:50.232 --> 35:51.231
you just never know.

35:51.275 --> 35:52.983
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

35:53.026 --> 35:54.151
- [grunts]

35:54.194 --> 35:57.112
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

35:57.156 --> 35:58.822
[grunts]

35:58.866 --> 36:01.908
[stalks thudding]

36:04.037 --> 36:06.204
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

36:06.248 --> 36:07.831
- [exhales deeply]

36:07.875 --> 36:09.374
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

36:09.418 --> 36:10.959
- It's got a lot of weight
to it.

36:11.003 --> 36:14.880
But obviously it's plenty sharp.

36:14.923 --> 36:16.923
Nicely done.
- Thank you.

36:16.967 --> 36:18.216
- All right, Stephan, you're up.
Are you ready?

36:18.260 --> 36:19.384
- Can't wait.

36:19.428 --> 36:20.927
Jay's weapon did really well

36:20.971 --> 36:22.053
cutting through the sugarcanes.

36:22.097 --> 36:23.388
<i> I'm not nervous about mine,</i>

36:23.432 --> 36:24.931
<i> but, you know, I don't know</i>

36:24.975 --> 36:25.849
<i> if it's gonna cut</i>
<i> better than his.</i>

36:25.893 --> 36:28.143
His cut real strong.

36:28.187 --> 36:29.186
♪ ♪

36:29.229 --> 36:30.312
- [grunts]

36:30.355 --> 36:33.190
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

36:33.233 --> 36:35.483
[grunts]

36:35.527 --> 36:37.235
[stalks thudding]

36:38.322 --> 36:39.821
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

36:39.865 --> 36:41.239
- It's light.
It's easy to wield.

36:41.283 --> 36:43.366
That guard--

36:43.410 --> 36:47.621
it's almost where it's into you
when you're swinging it.

36:47.664 --> 36:50.582
You can see it cut deep
and clean.

36:50.626 --> 36:52.584
It looks like the blade
held up beautifully.

36:52.628 --> 36:53.877
So, nice job.

36:53.921 --> 36:55.253
- Thank you.

36:55.297 --> 36:57.547
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

36:57.591 --> 37:00.592
- Bladesmiths, the Zweihander
was a weapon of war.

37:00.636 --> 37:02.719
Big weapon, big damage.

37:02.763 --> 37:04.804
I will take your weapon
and deliver killing blows

37:04.848 --> 37:06.514
on this ballistic dummy.

37:06.558 --> 37:08.642
Let's see how much damage
your weapon can do.

37:08.685 --> 37:09.976
Jay, you're up first.
You ready?

37:10.020 --> 37:12.103
- Go for it.
- Let's do this.

37:12.147 --> 37:15.065
<i> [suspenseful music]</i>

37:15.108 --> 37:21.613
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

37:21.657 --> 37:25.242
[sloshing]

37:25.285 --> 37:27.035
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

37:27.079 --> 37:28.954
- It is a heavy weight,

37:28.997 --> 37:32.499
and it's harder to manipulate
with multiple blows.

37:32.542 --> 37:34.167
But on the thrust,

37:34.211 --> 37:36.461
I was able to go in one side,

37:36.505 --> 37:40.257
and all the way out
the opposite side of the dummy.

37:40.300 --> 37:42.968
This, sir, will kill.

37:43.011 --> 37:44.511
- Thank you.

37:44.554 --> 37:46.388
- Stephan, you're up next.
You ready?

37:46.431 --> 37:48.515
- Absolutely.
- Let's do this.

37:48.558 --> 37:51.476
<i> [suspenseful music]</i>

37:51.520 --> 37:58.441
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

37:58.485 --> 37:59.776
<i> [squelching]</i>

37:59.820 --> 38:01.611
♪ ♪

38:01.655 --> 38:04.447
[sloshing]

38:04.491 --> 38:06.157
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

38:06.201 --> 38:08.034
- That was brutal.

38:08.078 --> 38:09.577
- Okay, Steve.

38:09.621 --> 38:12.580
The edge of your sword is
sharp enough

38:12.624 --> 38:15.166
to lacerate all the way
into the ribs.

38:15.210 --> 38:18.295
And on the power strike,
that would disembowel

38:18.338 --> 38:20.297
and ruin this person.

38:20.340 --> 38:22.007
- That's the idea.

38:22.050 --> 38:24.676
- This sword will kill.

38:24.720 --> 38:26.594
Good job.
- Thank you.

38:26.638 --> 38:28.221
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

38:28.265 --> 38:30.432
- Gentlemen,
this is the strength test.

38:30.475 --> 38:33.518
Now, the Zweihander was often
used against pike formations,

38:33.562 --> 38:35.395
so I'm gonna take
your Zweihanders

38:35.439 --> 38:37.939
and go against a rack of pikes
here

38:37.983 --> 38:39.774
five times
with each of your blades,

38:39.818 --> 38:42.110
see how far
it can break through.

38:42.154 --> 38:43.486
Jay, you're up.
Are you ready?

38:43.530 --> 38:45.864
- Ready.

38:45.907 --> 38:48.575
After two tests, Stephan and I
are pretty neck and neck,

38:48.618 --> 38:50.327
<i> so I feel pretty nervous,</i>

38:50.370 --> 38:52.662
<i> because this next test should</i>
<i> really determine</i>

38:52.706 --> 38:54.331
<i> who is gonna take home</i>
<i> the prize.</i>

38:54.374 --> 38:55.999
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

38:56.043 --> 38:57.334
[wood cracking]

38:57.377 --> 38:58.668
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

39:03.008 --> 39:04.799
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

39:04.843 --> 39:06.760
- Gentlemen,
this is the strength test.

39:06.803 --> 39:08.219
Jay, you're up. Are you ready?

39:08.263 --> 39:09.888
- Ready.

39:09.931 --> 39:12.807
<i> [driving rock music]</i>

39:12.851 --> 39:20.523
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

39:20.567 --> 39:21.858
- [grunts]

39:21.902 --> 39:23.777
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

39:23.820 --> 39:26.196
- Wow.
[chuckles]

39:26.239 --> 39:28.323
When you start
swinging this thing,

39:28.367 --> 39:30.658
it moves things out of its way.

39:30.702 --> 39:33.703
I don't see any damage
to your edge.

39:33.747 --> 39:35.080
Nicely done.

39:35.123 --> 39:36.289
- Thank you.

39:36.333 --> 39:37.916
- All right, Stephan, you're up.

39:37.959 --> 39:39.876
- Do it.
- Okay.

39:39.920 --> 39:41.294
<i> - The third test</i>
<i> is probably the one</i>

39:41.338 --> 39:43.046
I'm the most confident about.

39:43.090 --> 39:44.839
You know, I've beat the heck
out of this sword,

39:44.883 --> 39:46.800
and it's doing well,
so now it's just,

39:46.843 --> 39:49.135
"How much mayhem
can Dave cause?"

39:49.179 --> 39:52.013
<i> [driving rock music]</i>

39:52.057 --> 40:00.021
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

40:00.065 --> 40:02.941
<i> [rock music continues]</i>

40:02.984 --> 40:06.653
♪ ♪

40:06.696 --> 40:08.446
Obviously it's a good cutter.

40:08.490 --> 40:10.657
It actually bit into that wood
and split that

40:10.700 --> 40:12.242
right down the middle.

40:12.285 --> 40:15.995
Very easy to wield
because of its light weight.

40:16.039 --> 40:18.915
But I think we've bent
just a little bit.

40:18.959 --> 40:20.208
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

40:20.252 --> 40:22.168
<i> It's bent in two directions.</i>

40:22.212 --> 40:25.547
And there is a crack
now developing in the handle.

40:25.590 --> 40:27.590
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

40:27.634 --> 40:29.300
- Gentlemen,
we've got a lot to discuss.

40:29.344 --> 40:30.844
We'll see you back at the Forge.

40:30.887 --> 40:33.721
- I'm concerned.
I had a warp in my blade,

40:33.765 --> 40:36.558
so I don't know
who's gonna end up with the win.

40:36.601 --> 40:39.602
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

40:39.646 --> 40:42.230
- Bladesmiths, the judges
have made their final decision,

40:42.274 --> 40:43.815
but before I tell you
what that is,

40:43.859 --> 40:45.608
they have some feedback
for both of you.

40:45.652 --> 40:46.985
Jason?

40:47.028 --> 40:49.154
- Stephan, I really liked

40:49.197 --> 40:51.573
that you made a blade
out of Damascus.

40:51.616 --> 40:53.575
I also liked the weight
of your blade

40:53.618 --> 40:56.286
<i> and the symmetry</i>
<i> after the lugs.</i>

40:56.329 --> 40:58.288
<i> Overall, you did well.</i>

40:58.331 --> 41:00.290
It was a very difficult
challenge to go through.

41:00.333 --> 41:01.875
- Thank you.

41:01.918 --> 41:04.085
- Doug?
- Jay, you brought us

41:04.129 --> 41:06.796
a beautiful sword
that's very powerful.

41:06.840 --> 41:10.008
It is sharp where it obliterated
some of the pikes,

41:10.051 --> 41:12.260
<i> but it did not come apart.</i>

41:12.304 --> 41:14.220
<i> Though heavy,</i>
<i> it's within the parameters</i>

41:14.264 --> 41:16.181
<i> of what that sword would do.</i>

41:16.224 --> 41:18.099
It's wieldable,
and it does a lot of damage.

41:18.143 --> 41:20.310
Good work.
- Thank you.

41:20.353 --> 41:22.020
- It's time to declare
one of you

41:22.063 --> 41:23.229
the "Forged in Fire" champion.

41:23.273 --> 41:27.442
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

41:27.486 --> 41:28.735
Jay,

41:28.778 --> 41:29.986
congratulations.

41:30.030 --> 41:31.863
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

41:31.907 --> 41:35.533
Stephan, unfortunately,
your sword did not make the cut.

41:35.577 --> 41:37.452
Dave will explain.

41:37.496 --> 41:39.370
- Stephan, I think
what you did with your steel is

41:39.414 --> 41:41.372
visually stunning.

41:41.416 --> 41:44.709
But what this came down to
was the strength test.

41:44.753 --> 41:47.670
When your handle developed
a bend in two directions,

41:47.714 --> 41:50.924
<i> that caused a stress fracture</i>
<i> in the handle,</i>

41:50.967 --> 41:53.760
<i> as well as a slight bend</i>
<i> right where the lugs are.</i>

41:53.803 --> 41:55.762
And it's those reasons combined

41:55.805 --> 41:56.971
that are sending you home.

41:57.015 --> 41:58.515
- I understand.

41:58.558 --> 42:01.643
- Stephan,
please surrender your weapon.

42:01.686 --> 42:04.354
<i> - I'm disappointed.</i>
<i> I really wanted to win.</i>

42:04.397 --> 42:05.647
But that's okay.

42:05.690 --> 42:07.524
<i> I loved being at the Forge.</i>

42:07.567 --> 42:09.943
It's hot. It's dirty.
You'll smell funny.

42:09.986 --> 42:13.112
<i> But it is so rewarding.</i>

42:13.156 --> 42:14.697
- Jay, congratulations.

42:14.741 --> 42:16.282
You are the "Forged in Fire"
champion.

42:16.326 --> 42:17.909
Good job.
[applause]

42:17.953 --> 42:19.911
- Thank you.

42:19.955 --> 42:21.621
- How do you feel right now?
- Ugh!

42:21.665 --> 42:24.499
I feel like my heart's
about to burst out of my chest.

42:24.543 --> 42:26.000
- Well,
that's the heaviest weapon

42:26.044 --> 42:28.211
I've ever had to wield
in this competition.

42:28.255 --> 42:30.547
A very well balanced
and powerful weapon, too.

42:30.590 --> 42:32.006
- Thank you.

42:32.050 --> 42:33.258
- And the way you built
your handle--

42:33.301 --> 42:35.009
that tells me a lot

42:35.053 --> 42:36.928
about the way
that you make things.

42:36.972 --> 42:39.889
<i> The wood is fitted on</i>
<i> and then wrapped with leather</i>

42:39.933 --> 42:41.933
<i> with these reinforcing pieces</i>
<i> underneath.</i>

42:41.977 --> 42:43.726
<i> That's the proper way</i>
<i> to construct it.</i>

42:43.770 --> 42:45.853
- Thank you.

42:45.897 --> 42:48.189
- Well, Jay,
in exchange for that sword

42:48.233 --> 42:50.483
and those socks...
[laughter]

42:50.527 --> 42:52.819
You will be receiving that check
for $10,000.

42:52.862 --> 42:55.488
<i> - When they announced</i>
<i> that I was the winner,</i>

42:55.532 --> 42:57.073
it felt really good.

42:57.117 --> 42:58.950
I've had people tell me,
you know,

42:58.994 --> 42:59.993
"You're good at what you do,"
but I always have

43:00.036 --> 43:01.828
this kind of self-doubt.

43:01.871 --> 43:04.455
<i> To make it all the way</i>
<i>to the end and be the champion,</i>

43:04.499 --> 43:05.415
I'm so happy.

43:05.458 --> 43:06.749
[laughs]

43:06.793 --> 43:09.419
<i> ♪ ♪</i>
